      SUBROUTINE O2CONT(V,SIGMA,ALPHA,BETA)                             O2C  100                                                         
C                                                                       O2C  110                                                         
C     THIS ROUTINE IS DRIVEN BY FREQUENCY, RETURNING ONLY THE           O2C  120                                                         
C     O2 COEFFICIENTS, INDEPENDENT OF TEMPERATURE.                      O2C  130                                                         
C                                                                       O2C  140                                                         
C  *******************************************************************  O2C  150                                                         
C  *  THESE COMMENTS APPLY TO THE COLUME ARRAYS FOR:                 *  O2C  160                                                         
C  *       PBAR*UBAR(O2)                                             *  O2C  170                                                         
C  *       PBAR*UBAR(O2)*DT                                          *  O2C  180                                                         
C  *   AND PBAR*UBAR(O2)*DT*DT    WHERE:  DT=TBAR-220.               *  O2C  190                                                         
C  *  THAT HAVE BEEN COMPILED IN OTHER PARTS OF THE LOWTRAN CODE     *  O2C  200                                                         
C  *                                                                 *  O2C  210                                                         
C  *  LOWTRAN7 COMPATIBLE:                                           *  O2C  220                                                         
C  *  O2 CONTINUUM SUBROUTINE FOR 1395-1760CM-1                      *  O2C  230                                                         
C  *  MODIFIED BY G.P. ANDERSON, APRIL '88                           *  O2C  240                                                         
C  *                                                                 *  O2C  250                                                         
C  *  THE EXPONENTIAL TEMPERATURE EMPLOYED IN THE FASCOD2 ALGORITHM  *  O2C  260                                                         
C  *  (SEE BELOW) IS NOT READILY SUITABLE FOR LOWTRAN.  THEREFORE    *  O2C  270                                                         
C  *  THE EXPONENTIALS HAVE BEEN LINEARLY EXPANDED, KEEPING ONLY THE *  O2C  280                                                         
C  *  LINEAR AND QUADRATIC TERMS:                                    *  O2C  290                                                         
C  *                                                                 *  O2C  300                                                         
C  *  EXP(A*DT)=1.+ A*DT + (A*DT)**2/2. + ....                       *  O2C  310                                                         
C  *                                                                 *  O2C  320                                                         
C  *     EXP(B*DT*DT)=1.+ B*DT*DT + (B*DT*DT)**2/2. + ....           *  O2C  330                                                         
C  *                                                                 *  O2C  340                                                         
C  *  THE PRODUCT OF THE TWO TERMS IS:                               *  O2C  350                                                         
C  *                                                                 *  O2C  360                                                         
C  *     (1. + A*DT + (A*A/2. + B)*DT*DT )                           *  O2C  370                                                         
C  *                                                                 *  O2C  380                                                         
C  *  THIS EXPANSION ONLY WORKS WELL FOR SMALL VALUES OF X IN EXP(X) *  O2C  390                                                         
C  *                                                                 *  O2C  400                                                         
C  *  SINCE DT = T-220., THE APPROXIMATION IS VERY GOOD UNTIL        *  O2C  410                                                         
C  *  T.GT.260. OR DT.GT.40.   AT T=280, THE MAXIMUM ERRORS ARE STILL*  O2C  420                                                         
C  *  LESS THAN 10% BUT AT T=300, THOSE ERRORS ARE AS LARGE AS 20%   *  O2C  430                                                         
C  *******************************************************************  O2C  440                                                         
C                                                                       O2C  450                                                         
C     THE FOLLOWING COMMENTS ARE EXCERPTED DIRECTLY FROM FASCOD2        O2C  460                                                         
C                                                                       O2C  470                                                         
C      THIS SUBROUTINE CONTAINS THE ROGERS AND WALSHAW                  O2C  480                                                         
C      EQUIVALENT COEFFICIENTS DERIVED FROM THE THEORETICAL             O2C  490                                                         
C      VALUES SUPPLIED BY ROLAND DRAYSON. THESE VALUES USE              O2C  500                                                         
C      THE SAME DATA AS TIMOFEYEV AND AGREE WITH TIMOFEYEV'S RESULTS.   O2C  510                                                         
C      THE DATA ARE IN THE FORM OF STRENGTHS(O2SO) AND TWO              O2C  520                                                         
C      COEFFICIENTS (O2A & O2B),  WHICH ARE USED TO CORRECT FOR         O2C  530                                                         
C      TEMPERATURE. THE DEPENDENCY ON PRESSURE SQUARED                  O2C  540                                                         
C      IS CONTAINED IN THE P*WO2 PART OF THE CONSTANT.                  O2C  550                                                         
C      NOTE THAT SINCE THE COEFFICIENTS ARE FOR AIR, THE                O2C  560                                                         
C      THE STRENGTHS ARE DIVIDED BY THE O2 MIXING RATIO FOR             O2C  570                                                         
C      DRY AIR OF 0.20946 (THIS IS ASSUMED CONSTANT).                   O2C  580                                                         
C      ORIGINAL FORMULATION OF THE COEFFICIENTS WAS BY LARRY GORDLEY.   O2C  590                                                         
C      THIS VERSION WRITTEN BY EARL THOMPSON, JULY 1984.                O2C  600                                                         
